The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Barreto formula on the anvil
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: Mohun Bagan are trying to work on a face-saving formula for Jose Ramirez Barreto to resolve the existing crisis with the player. As a possible step, the decision of slapping a show-cause notice on Barreto charging him with anti-club action has been put on hold. The clubs assistant secretary Balaram Chowdhury on Tuesday urged him to join the team against Dempo. Im appealing him to join the team and I promise his causes will be heard properly and all his grievances will be met with to the best of our abilities. It has been learnt that Barreto was supposed to take up his case with the IFA, but backtracked from it. Chowdhury admitted he had heard of such a stand from the players end and added the club would co-operate with him to the fullest extent. He, however, warned that the club is exploring legal options. We are intent on giving Barreto till Wednesday to resolving the issue. Thereafter, well move accordingly, the official pointed out. Later, Barretos wife Veronica informed he has no plans of going back on his words and is determined to leave Mohun Bagan without playing any more.  Copyright 
